title: Anthony Trent, Master Criminal
creator: Wyndham Martyn
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description:
LibriVox recording of Anthony Trent, Master Criminal, by Wyndham Martyn. Read by Anna Simon. In 1918, Anthony Trent, a well-educated young man in his late twenties, lives an unsatisfactory life in a New York boarding house. He writes successful crime fiction stories, but this doesn't pay enough for him to do the things he wants. Things change when he starts to put his knowledge of crime to a practical use... It gets him into serious trouble before long. (Summary by Anna Simon)

The sequel to this book, The Secret of the Silver Car, is also available on Librivox.
